quran[20]{c,v,t,f}:
15,71,"Lot exclaimed in exasperation: "If you are bent on doing something, then here are my daughters."<sup foot_note="176990">1</sup>",footnotes:176990:In (E.N. 87 of Surah Houd), it has been explained what Prophet Lot (peace be upon him) meant by this. It may also be added that such words as these were uttered by an honorable man like him in the last resort, when all his entreaties and earnest requests had failed to prevent those people from their evil designs towards his guests.
15,72,"By your life, (O Prophet), they went about blindly stumbling in their intoxication."
15,73,"Then the mighty Blast caught them at sunrise,"
15,74,"and turned the land upside down, and rained down stones of baked clay. {1}",footnotes:1:These “stones of baked clay” might have been meteoric showers or volcanic eruptions that flew and rained upon them
15,75,"There are great Signs in this for those endowed with intelligence."
15,76,"The place (where this occurred) lies along a known route. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
15,77,"Verily there is a Sign in this for the believers."
15,78,"And the people of Aykah were also wrong-doers. {1}",footnotes:1:The people of Al-Aikah were the community of Prophet Shuaib (peace be upon him) and were called Midianites after the name of their capital city and their territory. As regards Al-Aikah
15,79,"So We chastised them. The desolate locations of both communities lie on a well-known highway. {1}",footnotes:1:Midian lay on the route from Hijaz to Palestine and Syria.
15,80,"Surely the people of al-Hijr {1} also rejected the Messengers, calling them liars.",footnotes:1:Al-Hijr was the capital city of the people of Thamud
15,81,"We also gave them Our Signs, yet they turned away from them."
15,82,"They used to hew out houses from the mountains {1} and lived in security.",footnotes:1:That is
15,83,"Then the Blast caught them in the morning"
15,84,"and whatever they had been earning proved of no avail."
15,85,"We have not created the heavens and the earth and all that is in between them except with Truth. {1} Surely the Hour will come. So, (O Muhammad), do graciously overlook them (despite their misdeeds).",footnotes:1:This was to reassure the Prophet (peace be upon him) that ultimately he would come out successful because he was propagating the truth
15,86,"Your Lord is indeed the Creator of all, the All-Knowing. {1}",footnotes:1:These attributes of Allah have been mentioned to reassure the Prophet (peace be upon him) as if to say: As Allah is the Creator
15,87,"We have indeed bestowed on you the seven oft-repeated verses {1} and the Great Qur'an. {2}",footnotes:1:These seven verses which are recited over and over again in every prescribed salat are the verses of Surah Al- Fatihah. Though some of the commentators are of the view that this Al-Mathani
15,88,"Do not even cast your eyes towards the worldly goods We have granted to different kinds of people, nor grieve over the state they are in, {1} but turn your loving attention to the believers instead,",footnotes:1:That is
15,89,"and clearly tell the unbelievers: "I am most certainly a plain warner,""
15,90,"even as We had sent warning to those who had divided their religion into fragments;"
